<bill id="DLM3251046" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ" year.imprint="2010" bill.no="220" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
  <billdetail>
    <title>Subordinate Legislation (Confirmation and Validation) Bill (No 2)</title>
    <billtype>Government Bill</billtype>
    <explnote id="DLM3251047" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" official="yes" rule-after="yes" rule-before="yes" bill.no="220" bill.type="government" stage="1" year="2010">
      <heading>Explanatory note</heading>
      <explnote.group>
        <heading>General policy statement</heading>
        <para>
          <text>This Bill's purpose is to prevent the lapse (expiry or deemed revocation) of certain subordinate legislation that, by virtue of the Acts under which it is made, lapses at a stated time unless earlier confirmed or validated by Act of Parliament.</text>
        </para>
      </explnote.group>
      <explnote.group>
        <heading>Clause by clause analysis</heading>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 1</emphasis></citation> states the Title the Bill will have when enacted.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <clause.desc>
          <para>
            <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 2</emphasis></citation> provides that the Bill, when enacted, comes into force on the day after the date on which it receives the Royal assent.</text>
          </para>
        </clause.desc>
        <explnote.part id="DLM3251048">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1  </label>
          <heading>General and technical provisions</heading>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 3</emphasis></citation> states the purpose of the Bill when enacted. Most subordinate legislation is confirmed, but the orders in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">clauses 13, 15, and 16</emphasis></citation> are validated and confirmed because the Acts under which they are made provide that they expire at a stated time unless earlier validated and confirmed. However, in the light of their purpose (to prevent expiry), the effect of the validations is limited by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">clause 4</emphasis></citation>.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 4</emphasis></citation> ensures, in the light of their purpose, which is only to prevent expiry of the orders validated, that the validations effected by <citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">clauses 13, 15, and 16</emphasis></citation> do not also cure any invalidity.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 5</emphasis></citation> ensures that the Bill, when enacted, binds the Crown.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 6</emphasis></citation> repeals the Subordinate Legislation (Confirmation and Validation) Act 2009, which is now spent.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
        </explnote.part>
        <explnote.part id="DLM3251049">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2  </label>
          <heading>Confirmations and validations</heading>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 7</emphasis> confirms regulations under the Animal Products Act 1999.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 8</emphasis> confirms an order under the Biosecurity Act 1993.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 9</emphasis> confirms an order under the Civil Aviation Act 1990.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 10</emphasis></citation> confirms 2 orders under the Commodity Levies Act 1990.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 11</emphasis></citation> confirms 2 orders under the Customs and Excise Act 1996.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 12</emphasis> confirms regulations under the Gambling Act 2003.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 13</emphasis></citation> validates and confirms— </text>
              <list>
                <item>
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
                  <para>
                    <text>an order made under the New Zealand Superannuation and Retirement Income Act 2001 and the Social Security Act 1964; and</text>
                  </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes"/>
                  <para>
                    <text>an order made under the Social Security Act 1964.</text>
                  </para>
                </item>
              </list>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text><emphasis style="italic">Clause 14</emphasis> confirms 2 orders under the Road User Charges Act 1977.</text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text>
                <citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 15</emphasis> validates and confirms 2 orders under the Tariff Act 1988.</citation>
              </text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
          <clause.desc>
            <para>
              <text>
                <citation jurisdiction="nz"><emphasis style="italic">Clause 16</emphasis> validates and confirms an order under the War Pensions Act 1954.</citation>
              </text>
            </para>
          </clause.desc>
        </explnote.part>
      </explnote.group>
    </explnote>
  </billdetail>
